annotationA: SAGA-associated factor 29kDa, isoform A; Methylated histone binding; histone acetyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: chromatin remodeling; histone acetylation
annotationB: TBP-associated factor 6 (Taf6) is part of the multisubunit basal transcription factor TFIID, and it might be important for its stability. It forms a histone-like pair with e(y)1. Taf6 is required during all stages of Drosophila development, but particularly imaginal disc development and gametogenesis
